condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I A. 4 (c) | Description :Each eligible Inkhundla shall enter into a PPA setting out itsobligations and entitlements with respect to Performance-Based Infrastructure Funding for sub-projects under Part A(i). | Due Date:31-May-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I A. 5 (c) | Description :Each Eligible ULG shall enter into a PPA setting out itsobligations and entitlements with respect to Performance-Based Infrastructure Grants for activities under Part B(i) of the project.| Due Date :31-May-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I A. 6 (c) | Description :The MP shall enter into a MoU with each Eligible Inkhundla for theimplementation of Part A(i) and an annual side letter to the MoU, specifying the agreed activities in the following Fiscal Year. |Due Date :31-May-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I A. 6 (c) | Description :The MP shall enter into a National Implementation Agreement withthe PST for the purposes of providing implementation support to Eligible Tinkhundla in carrying out Subprojects under Part A(i). |Due Date :31-May-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section V | Description :The Borrower shall make CIP transfers to ULGs for amounts of at least E25.000.000 during each year of Project implementation. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section 5.01 | Description :The Project Implementation Manual has been adopted in a manner satisfactory to theBank. | Due Date :30-Dec-2011

Finance Agreement :Section 5.01 | Description :The establishment of the PST has been completed including the appointment of itsprofessional staff under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Dec-2011
Finance Agreement :Section 5.01 | Description :The financial managements system for the Project has been put in place in a mannersatisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Dec-2011

title.narrative: Percent of targeted Tinkhundla completing annual budgets on time for submission to MTAD
Percent of targeted Tinkhundla signing annual sub-project execution side letters with MP
Number of people provided with access to all-season roads within a 500-meter range under the project
Percent of Tinkhundla receiving a score of 80 or above on their final performance assessments.
Percent of ULGs receiving a score of 80 or above on their final performance assessments
Percent of ULGs with completed, up-to-date road asset registries
Sub-projects carried out as a percent of sub-projects in agreed annual budgets (planned vs.actual)
Percent of ULGs having annual financial audits completed within six months of the end of the financial year and neither adverse nordisclaimed
Minimum percentage of operating budget allocated to asset maintenance
Development of recommendations for a sustainable local government financing framework
Number of beneficiaries benefiting from emergency response and recovery activities.
